BVRIT HYDERABAD COLLEGE OF ENGINEERING FOR WOMEN
College Knowledge Base — RAG Grounding Document
Compiled from official sources (bvrithyderabad.edu.in) — July 2026
1. About BVRIT Hyderabad
History
BVRIT HYDERABAD College of Engineering for Women is an autonomous engineering college established in 2012 under the Sri Vishnu Educational Society (SVES), founded by Chairman Sri K. V. Vishnu Raju. It is the youngest institution under the SVES umbrella, created specifically to educate and empower women in engineering. The college began with an intake of 240 students across four branches (EEE, ECE, CSE, IT) and has since grown to an undergraduate intake of 660 across five B.Tech branches, plus postgraduate programmes.
Vision
To emerge as one of the best institutes of technology and research in the country, dedicated to promoting quality technical education.
Mission
●	Achieve academic excellence through innovative learning practices.
●	Enhance intellectual ability and technical competency for a successful career.
●	Encourage research and innovation.
●	Nurture students towards holistic development, with emphasis on leadership skills, life skills, and human values.
Accreditations & Approvals
●	NAAC: Accredited with Grade 'A' (2020).
●	NBA: Accredited for EEE, ECE, and CSE undergraduate programmes.
●	UGC Autonomous status granted from Academic Year 2023-24, for a period of 10 years.
●	Approved by AICTE (All India Council for Technical Education) and the Government of Telangana.
●	Affiliated to Jawaharlal Nehru Technological University, Hyderabad (JNTUH).
The college is one of the educational institutions of the Sri Vishnu Educational Society (SVES), which also runs several other engineering, pharmacy, dental, and school institutions across Andhra Pradesh and Telangana (the 'Green Meadows', 'Orchard Park', 'Valley Vista', and 'Lake View' campuses).












2. Departments
BVRIT Hyderabad offers undergraduate (B.Tech), postgraduate (M.Tech), and Ph.D research programmes through the following departments:
B.Tech (Undergraduate) Branches
●	Computer Science & Engineering (CSE)
●	Computer Science & Engineering — Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning (CSE-AI&ML / CSM)
●	Electronics and Communication Engineering (ECE)
●	Electrical and Electronics Engineering (EEE)
●	Information Technology (IT)
Total UG intake across these five branches: 660 seats (as per the official 'About BVRITH' page). Note: some third-party listings quote a lower overall UG intake figure (540); the college's own site states 660 including the CSE-AI&ML programme.
M.Tech (Postgraduate) Programmes
●	M.Tech — Data Sciences (intake: 18)
●	M.Tech — Computer Science and Engineering (intake: 12)
●	M.Tech — VLSI Design (intake: 12)
Ph.D / Research Centres
●	ECE (VLSI–Communications)
●	CSE
●	A dedicated 'Faculty as Ph.D Supervisors' programme for research guidance
Other Academic Units
●	Basic Sciences and Humanities (BS&H) — supports first-year foundational courses across all branches.
●	Honor Degree Programme — additional credentials for high-performing students.
Exact department-wise faculty headcounts are not published as a single consolidated figure on the college website; the site instead lists faculty individually under each department's page. This knowledge base does not fabricate a total faculty count.
3. Admissions
Eligibility
Candidates must have passed the 10+2 (Intermediate) examination with Mathematics, Physics, and Chemistry (MPC) as major subjects, with a minimum aggregate as prescribed by the Telangana State admissions authority (commonly cited as 60% aggregate, subject to category-wise relaxation).
Entrance Exams
●	TS EAMCET / TG EAPCET — primary entrance exam for B.Tech admissions (Convener quota / Category-A seats).
●	JEE Main — accepted by some listings as an alternate route for B.Tech admission.
●	TS PGECET / GATE — for M.Tech admissions.
Admission Categories
●	Category A: Seats filled through the Convener of TS EAMCET/TG EAPCET counselling (centralised counselling process).
●	Category B: Management-quota seats filled directly by the college as per TSCHE (Telangana State Council of Higher Education) guidelines.
Admission Process (typical flow)
●	Appear for TS EAMCET/TG EAPCET (or JEE Main, where applicable).
●	Participate in state counselling and exercise web options for Category-A seats, or apply directly to the college for Category-B (management quota) seats.
●	Complete document verification and fee payment as per the seat allotment.
College Codes
●	EAMCET / ECET code: BVRW
●	PGECET code: BVRW1
Key Contacts for Admissions
Professor In-Charge, Admissions: Dr. J. Manoj Kumar — Phone: 92471 64714 (as listed on the official site's admissions announcement).
Exact admission opening/closing dates change every academic year and are published on the TS EAMCET/TG EAPCET counselling portal and the college's own Admission Process page; this document does not fix a specific date so it does not go stale.
4. Fee Structure
B.Tech Tuition Fee — Official College Table (as published on bvrithyderabad.edu.in/admission/fee-details)
Batch	Branch(es)	Tuition Fee (₹/yr)	NBA Fee (₹/yr)	JNTUH/Misc. Fee (₹/yr)
2025	CSE, ECE, EEE, CSM	1,20,000	3,000 (CSM: –)	5,500
2024	CSE, ECE, EEE, CSM	1,20,000	3,000 (CSM: –)	5,500
2023	CSE, ECE, IT, EEE, CSM	1,20,000	3,000 (CSM: –)	5,500
2022	CSE, ECE, IT, EEE, CSM	1,20,000	3,000 (CSM: –)	2,500
2021	CSE, ECE, IT, EEE, CSM	90,000	3,000 (CSM: –)	5,500

For the current (2025) batch, the CSE, ECE, and EEE tuition fee is ₹1,20,000/year plus a ₹3,000/year NBA fee and ₹5,500/year JNTUH/miscellaneous fee, totaling roughly ₹1,28,500/year under the Convenor (Category-A) quota. The CSM (CSE-AI&ML) branch does not carry the NBA fee line since it is not yet NBA-accredited.
Other Fees (third-party aggregator estimates — verify with the college before relying on these)
●	Management-quota (Category-B) tuition: reported in the range of ₹1,20,000–₹1,50,000/year, depending on branch and source.
●	Hostel fees: reported in the range of roughly ₹70,000–₹1,20,000/year depending on room type and source.
●	Optional transport fee: reported around ₹18,000–₹40,000/year depending on route and source.
●	M.Tech PGECET application/registration fee: ₹1,100 (₹600 for SC/ST/PH candidates) per test, as per TS PGECET norms.
Scholarships
●	Telangana State Fee Reimbursement Scheme (government scholarship, income- and rank-linked).
●	Merit-based scholarships/fee waivers for top TS EAMCET/TG EAPCET rankers.
●	AICTE-administered scholarships such as the Pragati Scholarship for Girl Students (Technical Degree), the Saksham Scholarship for Specially Abled Students, and the AICTE Swanath Scholarship Scheme — all applied for via the National Scholarship Portal.
●	SC/ST fee concessions for students whose family income is below the prescribed threshold (commonly cited as ₹2 lakh/year).
●	PM Vidyalaxmi Scheme — education loan support, publicised on the official site.
The exact fee figures above beyond the official college table are sourced from third-party education portals (Collegedunia, Careers360, Shiksha, Propelld) and can vary by year and source; where the college's own published table and an aggregator disagree, the official college table (bvrithyderabad.edu.in) should be treated as authoritative.
5. Placements
Placement Cell
BVRIT Hyderabad's Training & Placement Cell is led by Sri. S. Jagapathi Reddy (Manager, Placements) and Sri. K. Mahesh Babu (Asst. Manager, Placements). There is also a central placement cell under the Sri Vishnu Educational Society that supports students across all SVES colleges with guidance and job-seeking support.
2021–2025 Batch Placement Summary
●	Total students placed: 614 (across EEE, ECE, CSE, IT, and CSE-AI&ML).
●	Highest package: ₹54.00 LPA (Microsoft).
●	Notable high-package recruiters: Visa (₹32.88 LPA / ₹31.64 LPA), Optum (₹20.78 LPA), Synopsys (₹20.26 LPA), Swiss Re (₹14 LPA).
●	High-volume recruiters: Capgemini SE (175 offers), Infosys SE (70), Tech Mahindra (71), Cognizant GenC (57), UST (33).
