Other Metrics
●	As per the NIRF 2026 report, 400 B.Tech and 9 M.Tech students were offered placements in 2025.
●	Average package for the 2025 batch is reported around ₹9.26 LPA by third-party sources; the average package for the top 25% of students was reported at ₹13.06 LPA.
Batch-wise placement PDFs (2017-21 through 2021-25) are published on the official Placement Details page and contain the full company-and-package breakdown by branch; the figures above are a summary. Package and headcount figures for batches before 2021 are sourced from the same official page's scanned/tabulated placement reports.
6. Campus & Facilities
Library
Housed in a four-storey building called the Ruby Block, the library serves as the college's intellectual hub. It holds textbooks, reference books, journals, and competitive-exam resources, and is a member of DELNET and the National Digital Library of India (NDLI). Materials are organised using the Dewey Decimal Classification (DDC) system.
●	Library hours: 9:00 AM – 6:00 PM; Issue & Return: 10:00 AM – 5:00 PM.
●	Digital library: 10 internet-enabled computers with access to NPTEL lectures and online mock tests.
●	E-resources: IEEE Xplore, J-Gate, DELNET, accessible remotely via the Knimbus e-library platform and mLibrary mobile app.
●	Plagiarism-check service using iThenticate (Turnitin) for staff and student publications.
●	Rare book collection dating from 1919 onwards; a dedicated Book Bank for SC/ST students.
Laboratories
Each engineering department maintains dedicated laboratories aligned with its curriculum; the college also runs several specialised labs and centres as 'differentiators', including an IoT Maker Space, a Drone Technology Laboratory, and an Assistive Technology Lab (ATL).
Hostel
On-campus hostel accommodation is available across 4 blocks with 150+ rooms and capacity for 500+ students. Facilities include 24/7 water supply, geysers, round-the-clock security with lady wardens, a common room, gym area, TV/entertainment area, and an anti-ragging squad. A full-time lady physical director organises outdoor sports such as volleyball, badminton, and throw-ball.
Sports
The college has a dedicated Sports Club and physical-education staff supporting outdoor games (volleyball, badminton, throw-ball, etc.) and fitness activities, both for hostel residents and day scholars.
Wi-Fi & IT Infrastructure
Campus-wide Wi-Fi and computer labs are available; student reviews consistently describe classrooms as equipped with boards/projectors and functioning Wi-Fi.
Transportation
The college (via the broader BVRIT/SVES network) operates a private bus fleet — approximately 14 routes — covering various parts of Hyderabad, with buses equipped with GPS/GPRS tracking for student safety. Transport is optional and charged separately from tuition.
Other Campus Facilities
●	Food & Cafeteria — on-campus dining options.
●	Gym — fitness facility for students.
●	Temple — on-campus place of worship.
●	Security — round-the-clock campus security.
●	Medical/health support — reported by students as part of standard campus facilities.
●	PCS (Placement & Career Success) facilities.
●	600-seat-class auditorium and seminar halls for events (shared infrastructure noted across the SVES network).
