Department-wise Faculty Strength & Heads of Department
Faculty strength and department leadership, as published on each department's 'About the Department' page (bvrithyderabad.edu.in):
●	Computer Science & Engineering (CSE): 49 faculty members — 7 Professors, 6 Associate Professors, and 36 Assistant Professors — supplemented by adjunct faculty from industry and academia. Faculty specialisations span Machine Learning, Computer Networks, Data Mining, Image Processing, Parallel Computing, Software Engineering, Cloud Computing, Soft Computing, Blockchain, Deep Learning, and Artificial Intelligence.
●	Electronics & Communication Engineering (ECE): Faculty are diversified across Communications, Signal Processing, and VLSI & Embedded Systems. Dr Vasu Babu, Professor, ECE, was listed among the world's top 2% of scientists (2024 ranking) in Information & Communication Technologies, released by Elsevier and Stanford University.
●	Electrical & Electronics Engineering (EEE): Headed by Dr. B. Srinivasa Rao, M.Tech., Ph.D, a Senior Member of IEEE, a Fellow of IE (FIE), and a Life Member of ISTE (LMISTE). He has completed two funded research projects worth Rs. 13.8 lakh, with research interests in power system optimization, renewable energy systems, multi-objective optimization, deregulated power systems, and optimal operation with FACTS devices.
●	Information Technology (IT): Faculty are described as highly motivated with a strong research orientation; the department holds Centre of Excellence status in Data Science. Exact headcount is not published as a single figure on the department page.
●	CSE – Artificial Intelligence & Machine Learning (AI&ML) and Basic Sciences & Humanities (BS&H): Each maintains its own faculty listing under its department's 'About the Department' and 'Faculty' pages; individual faculty rosters, qualifications and specialisations are not consolidated into a single site-wide directory.
Every department page also names an individual 'About HOD' page (e.g. bvrithyderabad.edu.in/[department]/about-hod/) and a dedicated 'Faculty' listing page; the full name and designation of every faculty member from these pages is reproduced in the ‘Complete Faculty Roster’ section below. Faculty across departments are encouraged to pursue certifications via NPTEL-SWAYAM, Coursera, edX, NASSCOM, and similar platforms, and several have received recognitions such as the AIMERS Best Faculty Award and inclusion in Stanford/Elsevier's world top 2% scientists list.
